> In this case, there&#x27;s also the problem that &#x27;Stream&#x27; is already used by node.<p>Haha, well, your grandparent would like you to know that&#x27;s no reason to avoid a particular name.  Module system!  ;)<p><pre><code>  > var BoringStream = require(&#x27;stream&#x27;);
  > var Stream = require(&#x27;highland&#x27;);
</code></pre>
Or if we like special chars, we could get really cute:<p><pre><code>  > var $tream = require(&#x27;highland&#x27;);
</code></pre>
It&#x27;s like Stream, but, you know, blingier.

TIL why<p><pre><code>    class Foo<T> {

        void test(Foo<T> f) {
            // ...
        }

        static void boom() {
            Foo<?> f = new Foo<String>();
            f.test(f); // <--- boom! compile error
        }
    }</code></pre>
